primary.title: The Philippines Has the World's Longest Christmas Celebration
primary.description: Perhaps no country on Earth loves Christmas more than the Philippines. Residents there celebrate the holiday for four months solid. Here's why.

secondary.title: 6 Christmas traditions that only Filipinos can relate to
secondary.description: One thing about Filipinos is they like everything flashy at Christmas. They go big or go home.

secondary.title: Pinoy faithful gather for 9-day Simbang Gabi
secondary.description: The traditional pre-dawn novena masses, popularly known as “Simbang Gabi” in the Philippines, will officially start today.

secondary.title: In The Philippines Christmas Eve Includes A Late-Night Street Food Feast - Tasting Table
secondary.description: The Philippines are known for all-out celebrations, and Christmas Eve is no different thanks to the late-night street food tradition of Noche Buena.

carousel.title: ‘It’s been a long time coming’: The Bay Area’s Filipino baking scene is more exciting than ever
carousel.description: Ube pies, cheesy ensaymadas and so much more.
